[5] Guatemala
Date: Wed 19 Aug 2009
Source: Prensa Libre [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.prensalibre.com/pl/2009/agosto/19/336292.html>


The Ministry of Health today [19 Aug 2009] declared a red alert due
to an outbreak of classical dengue and DHF, which has caused the
deaths of at least 5 children. This measure [red alert] was adopted
due to the proliferation of patients suspected of having dengue
[virus infection], which has saturated the hospitals and clinics in
the Izabal department [state or province equivalent]. La Prenza has
reported that some 700 children have been seen daily in the Eliza
Martinez National Hospital in Izabal, half of whom have symptoms of
dengue, and at least 30 were hospitalized.

Last week [week of 9 Aug 2009], the outbreak was recognized as
affecting the Caribbean coastal populations, which [caused] the
Ministry of Health to send a mission [there] to evaluate the
situation and declare a red alert to deal with the emergency.

--
